@@TJvCommStatus.ClearToSend
Description:
This property is true when the "Data Set Ready" has been found in the control register of the modem. (CTS)

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCommStatus.Comm
Description:
This is the comm port you want to spy. Specify cpNOCOM if you don't want to spy any port (The thread is paused).

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCommStatus.DataSetReady
Description:
This property is true when the "Clear To Send" has been found in the control register of the modem. (DSR)

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCommStatus.OnChanged
Description:
This event is called when the status of the modem has changed. The modem is spyed through a separated thread, with a latency of 50ms.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCommStatus.ReceiveLine
Description:
This property is true when the "Receive Line Signal Detect" has been found in the control register of the modem. (RLSD)

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCommStatus.Ring
Description:
This property is true when the "Ring Indicator" has been found in the control register of the modem.

